A report from Mac Otakara cites a source who says that it’s possible that the iPhone SE 2 is actually named iPhone 9.

The iPhone 9, or iPhone SE 2, is rumored to sport a 4.7-inch LCD display, bezels, an actual Home button and Touch ID, A13 Bionic chipset and 3GB of RAM.

It’s also rumored to retain a single-lens camera setup and, like Apple’s other recent handsets, will probably ditch 3D Touch in favor of Haptic Touch. ————————————
